
[1]fearful

   FE'ARFUL, a.

   1. Affected by fear; feeling pain in expectation of evil; apprehensive
   with solicitude; afraid. I am fearful of the consequences of rash
   conduct. Hence,

   2. Timid; timorous; wanting courage.

   What man is there that is fearful and fainthearted?

                                  Deut. 20.

   3. Terrible; impressing fear; frightful; dreadful.

   It is a fearful thing to fall into the hands of the living God. Heb.
   10.

   4. Awful; to be reverenced.

   O Lord, who is like thee, glorious in holiness, fearful in praises? Ex.
   15.

   That thou mayest fear this glorious and fearful name, Jehovah, thy God.
   Deut. 28.
